    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Justin M. Keyes said in #2977 : \r\n> Why are you exporting `VIMRUNTIME`? Even the Vim docs mention that it is not recommended,\r\n\r\nThe nvim documentation actually says:\r\n> You don't normally set `$VIMRUNTIME` yourself\r\n\r\nContrary to this recommendation, nvim itself _does_ export this environment variable, to everything run in a terminal.  This of course could include vim or even another instance of nvim.  It similarly exports `VIM`.\r\n\r\nSee `:terminal printenv VIMRUNTIME`  and `:terminal printenv VIM` ",
    "closed_at": "2023-12-07T21:02:03Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, we shouldn't do this. I think the best approach is to unset it unconditionally, and `jobstart()` should gain the [ability to sent env vars](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/4970).",
