            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Actually based on my observations Vim adds VIM and VIMRUNTIME environment variables while Neovim adds VIMRUNTIME and NVIM_LISTEN_ADDRESS environment variables if you check at `--cmd`. `VIM` environment variable is added by Neovim if it was somehow accessed (e.g. `nvim -u NONE -i NONE -c '!env > /tmp/nvim.env' -c cq` does not add it, but without `-u NONE` it does), same for `MYVIMRC` (with my setup without `-u NONE` I see adding VIMRUNTIME, NVIM_LISTEN_ADDRESS, VIM, MYVIMRC in Neovim (only standard plugins plus powerline which now fails with exception because I am not on editors-refactor branch currently); VIMRUNTIME, VIM, MYVIMRC, XDG_DATA_HOME, LC_MESSAGES, LC_ALL in Vim (many plugins)).",
